results.name: Numerator of b(n), where b(1)=b(2)=1, and for n>2, b(n) = (1+b(n-2))/b(n-1).
comment: With a tiny change in subscripts {b(n)} becomes the Lyness 5-cycle, a sequence of period 5, as illustrated in A076839.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jul 17 2020
